Marina Sitrin reads extracts from her book '[[Horizontalism]]'. The book is a collection of first-hand accounts by people involved in various forms of ground-up social re-organisation that was initiated by ordinary people in the wake of Argentina's economic collapse in 2001.

The video was recorded at the Radical Independent Bookfair event in Glasgow - http://www.ribproject.

Audio via http://www.archive.org/details/MarinaSitrinReadingFromHorizontalism




